---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Bridger | Levenhall" description="Bridger is Levenhall's pre-RFP intelligence platform for US federal contracting — built first for allied technology firms.">

    <!-- ── HERO ── -->
    <section class="b-hero">
        <div class="b-hero-bg"></div>
        <div class="b-hero-inner">
            <p class="b-tag">A Levenhall Product</p>
            <img src="/images/products/bridger-logo.png" alt="Bridger" class="b-logo">
            <p class="b-tagline">Market Entry Intelligence for US Federal Contracting</p>
            <div class="b-cta">
                <a href="https://bridger.levenhall.com" class="btn btn-gold" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Bridger</a>
                <a href="https://bridger.levenhall.com/brief" class="btn btn-outline-white" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Daily Brief</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── OPENING ── -->
    <section class="b-section b-opening">
        <div class="b-narrow reveal">
            <p class="b-lede">The US federal government will spend roughly $750 billion this year. By the time any of it shows up on SAM.gov, it has already been decided.</p>
            <p>Appropriations bills, committee markups, agency forecasts, GAO bid protests, OFAC entity-list updates, allied defense reorganizations &mdash; the signal that decides who wins moves six to twelve months ahead of the RFP. Incumbent contractors pay fifty thousand dollars a year for that signal. Everyone else competes blind.</p>
            <p>For allied technology firms it is worse still. They arrive cold into a regulatory landscape they don't speak &mdash; ITAR, FOCI, CFIUS, DSGL, DISP &mdash; and the partners who could shorten the path are invisible without a local network.</p>
            <p class="b-lede-close">Bridger is the platform we built so they don't have to.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── WHAT IT IS — DOCUMENT STYLE ── -->
    <section class="b-doc">
        <div class="b-doc-bg"></div>
        <div class="b-doc-inner">
            <div class="b-doc-header reveal">
                <span class="b-doc-eyebrow">§ Structure</span>
                <h2>A three-part system, in the order it works.</h2>
            </div>

            <article class="b-doc-item reveal">
                <span class="b-doc-num">01</span>
                <div class="b-doc-body">
                    <h3>Intelligence &mdash; the spine.</h3>
                    <p>Roughly twenty-three hundred procurement-relevant signals flow into the index every week. SAM.gov, FPDS, GAO, OFAC, Congress.gov, agency forecasts, CISA and NIST, allied defense ministries, ACLED, the Federal Register, executive orders, congressional hearings.</p>
                    <p>A clustering layer running on Claude Haiku synthesizes them into assessments &mdash; about a thousand in the index at any time, each confidence-rated, source-cited, country-tagged. A Country Instability Index scores the markets that matter. Every new opportunity is matched against a contractor's profile across five separate signals, and the system will not generate a rationale unless at least two of those signals actually fired.</p>
                    <p>The daily brief is free, public, and lands at six in the morning Eastern.</p>
                </div>
            </article>

            <article class="b-doc-item reveal">
                <span class="b-doc-num">02</span>
                <div class="b-doc-body">
                    <h3>Marketplace &mdash; the network.</h3>
                    <p>Three search surfaces on one fit-scoring engine. <strong>Provider Search</strong> for the people you need to win &mdash; C3PAOs, proposal writers, US incorporation specialists, 8(a) JV partners, contract manufacturers. <strong>Lobbyist Search</strong> for the people who shape what gets written. <strong>Tech Scout</strong> for the fourteen hundred allied technology firms already vetted across sixty-plus countries.</p>
                    <p>Same scoring algorithm; per-surface filters. Warm introductions at the point of intent, not a separate CRM you have to remember to open.</p>
                </div>
            </article>

            <article class="b-doc-item reveal">
                <span class="b-doc-num">03</span>
                <div class="b-doc-body">
                    <h3>Capture &mdash; the workflow.</h3>
                    <p>A pipeline kanban that knows what stage you're in: <em>Identified, Qualified, Capture, Proposal, Submitted.</em> An AI-generated capture brief built from the opportunity, your company record, and the match intelligence. A capability statement and past performance that auto-populate from one canonical record &mdash; so nothing drifts.</p>
                    <p>It is the gap between <em>I'm watching this</em> and <em>I'm submitting on this</em>, closed.</p>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── ALLIED MOAT — INLINE ── -->
    <section class="b-section b-moat">
        <div class="b-narrow reveal">
            <span class="b-eyebrow">§ The allied moat</span>
            <h2>The compliance regimes other tools won't touch.</h2>
            <p>Bridger indexes the regulatory regimes that govern who can sell what, side by side. <span class="b-moat-tag">🇺🇸 ITAR</span> with AUKUS Final Rule (§ 126.7) eligibility tracking. <span class="b-moat-tag">🇺🇸 FOCI</span> mitigation under NISPOM and DCSA, and <span class="b-moat-tag">🇺🇸 CFIUS</span> review under 50 U.S.C. § 4565. <span class="b-moat-tag">🇺🇸 ECCN</span> classification and BIS licensing. <span class="b-moat-tag">🇦🇺 DSGL</span> and <span class="b-moat-tag">🇦🇺 DISP</span> on the Australian side. <span class="b-moat-tag">🇬🇧 List X</span> and Security Cleared status on the UK side.</p>
            <p class="b-moat-close">No general procurement tool tracks these together. That's the layer that makes allied entry tractable, and it's the structural reason &mdash; not the marketing reason &mdash; that the platform was built for allied firms first.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── DIFFERENTIATION ── -->
    <section class="b-section b-diff">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="b-header reveal">
                <span class="b-eyebrow b-eyebrow-center">§ The short version</span>
                <h2>What you get that you can't get elsewhere.</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="b-diff-table reveal">
                <div class="b-diff-row b-diff-head">
                    <span></span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">Bridger</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">Most procurement tools</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Signal timing</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">Pre-RFP signal, forecasts, appropriations</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">RFP listings after SAM.gov publishes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Matching</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">5-signal scoring with cited rationales</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">Keyword search</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Cross-border</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">ITAR / FOCI / CFIUS / DSGL / DISP, together</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">US-only</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Marketplace</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">Warm intros inside the intelligence</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">Standalone directory or separate CRM</span>
                </div>
                <div class="b-diff-row">
                    <span class="b-diff-cap">Audience</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-mark">Allied technology firms entering the US</span>
                    <span class="b-diff-other">US-only contractors</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection
        heading="Open Bridger."
        description="Production at bridger.levenhall.com. Free daily brief at 6 AM Eastern. Scout tier is free."
        primaryLabel="Open Bridger"
        primaryHref="https://bridger.levenhall.com"
        secondaryLabel="Daily Brief"
        secondaryHref="https://bridger.levenhall.com/brief"
    />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
    /* ── HERO ── */
    .b-hero {
        background: linear-gradient(160deg, #060c18 0%, #0c1628 40%, #0a1224 100%);
        padding: 9rem 2rem 5rem;
        text-align: center;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .b-hero-bg {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at 50% 80%, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.06) 0%, transparent 55%);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .b-hero::after {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        bottom: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--gold), transparent);
        opacity: 0.5;
    }

    .b-hero-inner {
        max-width: 620px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .b-tag {
        display: inline-block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.66rem;
        letter-spacing: 3.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 1.8rem;
    }

    .b-logo {
        max-width: 360px;
        width: 100%;
        height: auto;
        display: block;
        margin: 0 auto 1.6rem;
    }

    .b-tagline {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
        margin-bottom: 2rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    }

    .b-cta {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    /* ── SHARED ── */
    .b-section {
        padding: 6rem 0;
    }

    .b-eyebrow {
        display: block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        letter-spacing: 2.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .b-eyebrow-center {
        text-align: center;
    }

    .b-narrow {
        max-width: 660px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .b-narrow h2 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
    }

    /* ── OPENING ── */
    .b-opening {
        background: var(--cream);
        padding: 6.5rem 0;
    }

    .b-lede {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        line-height: 1.45;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        margin-bottom: 1.6rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .b-lede-close {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--burgundy);
        margin-top: 2rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding-top: 1.6rem;
    }

    .b-opening p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    /* ── DOCUMENT-STYLE STRUCTURE SECTION ── */
    .b-doc {
        background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0a1628 0%, var(--deep-navy) 100%);
        padding: 6rem 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    .b-doc-bg {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        background-image: radial-gradient(ellipse at 70% 30%, rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.05) 0%, transparent 50%);
        pointer-events: none;
    }

    .b-doc::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        top: 0;
        left: 0;
        right: 0;
        height: 1px;
        background: rgba(201, 169, 97, 0.25);
    }

    .b-doc-inner {
        max-width: 820px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .b-doc-header {
        margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
        padding-bottom: 2rem;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    }

    .b-doc-eyebrow {
        display: block;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.72rem;
        letter-spacing: 2.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .b-doc-header h2 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.3rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: #fff;
    }

    .b-doc-item {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
        gap: 2rem;
        padding: 2.2rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    }

    .b-doc-item:last-of-type {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    .b-doc-num {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: 3rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gold);
        line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
        text-align: right;
        padding-top: 0.4rem;
    }

    .b-doc-body h3 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #fff;
        margin: 0 0 0.9rem;
        line-height: 1.3;
    }

    .b-doc-body p {
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.85;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
        margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .b-doc-body p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .b-doc-body strong {
        color: #fff;
        font-weight: 600;
    }

    .b-doc-body em {
        font-style: italic;
        color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    }

    /* ── MOAT ── */
    .b-moat {
        background: var(--stone);
        padding: 6rem 0;
    }

    .b-moat h2 {
        color: var(--deep-navy);
    }

    .b-moat p {
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.95;
        color: var(--text-medium);
        margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    .b-moat-tag {
        display: inline;
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
        margin: 0 0.1rem;
        white-space: nowrap;
        font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    .b-moat-close {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: var(--burgundy);
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border-warm);
        padding-top: 1.4rem;
        margin-top: 0.6rem;
    }

    /* ── DIFFERENTIATION ── */
    .b-diff {
        background: var(--cream);
    }

    .b-header {
        max-width: 660px;
        margin: 0 auto 3rem;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .b-header h2 {
        font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 3vw, 2.2rem);
        line-height: 1.25;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        font-weight: 700;
    }

    .b-diff-table {
        max-width: 940px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .b-diff-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 0.7fr 1.4fr 1fr;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        padding: 1.3rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(30, 58, 95, 0.12);
        align-items: center;
        font-size: 1rem;
        line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .b-diff-row:last-child {
        border-bottom: none;
    }

    .b-diff-head {
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--deep-navy);
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.7rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 2px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding-bottom: 0.9rem;
    }

    .b-diff-head .b-diff-mark { color: var(--burgundy); }
    .b-diff-head .b-diff-other { color: var(--text-medium); }

    .b-diff-cap {
        font-family: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif;
        font-size: 0.78rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 1.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--deep-navy);
    }

    .b-diff-mark {
        color: var(--deep-navy);
        font-weight: 500;
    }

    .b-diff-other {
        color: var(--text-medium);
        font-style: italic;
    }

    /* ── RESPONSIVE ── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .b-hero { padding: 7rem 2rem 4rem; }
        .b-logo { max-width: 280px; }
        .b-section { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .b-opening { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .b-doc { padding: 4.5rem 0; }
        .b-doc-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.8rem; padding: 2rem 0; }
        .b-doc-num { text-align: left; font-size: 2.2rem; padding-top: 0; }
        .b-lede { font-size: 1.3rem; }
        .b-diff-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.3rem; padding: 1.2rem 0; }
        .b-diff-head { display: none; }
        .b-diff-cap { color: var(--burgundy); }
    }
</style>
